<exercise number="29"><statement><p>You deposit $1000 in a savings account paying 5% interest compounded continuously.<ol>
        <li><p>Find the amount in the account after 7 years.</p></li>
        <li><p>How long will it take for the original principal to double?</p></li>
        <li><p>Find a formula for the time <m>t</m> required for the amount to reach <m>A</m>.</p></li>
    </ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol cols="3">
    <li><p>$1419.07</p></li>
    <li><p>13.9 years</p></li>
    <li><p><m>t = 20 \ln\left(\dfrac{A}{1000} \right)</m></p></li>
</ol></p></answer></exercise>

